A suicide bombing at a shopping mall near Israel's nuclear reactor marked the first attack on Israeli soil since peace talks resumed.
The breach of the Egypt-Gaza border raised concerns of militants entering Israel.
The bombing in Dimona killed one and injured 11, sparking panic.
Palestinian groups claimed responsibility, with ties to Fatah and Hamas.
The bombers may have entered from Egypt, bypassing the Gaza border.
Israeli security forces remain on high alert, fearing further attacks.
The incident underscores the ongoing conflict and the need for peace negotiations to continue despite the violence.
